00:53:47.530 --> 00:53:50.910
And that's what it was doing for
you with putting this cutoff.

00:53:50.910 --> 00:53:52.690
MS-bar was having problems at 0.

00:53:52.690 --> 00:53:56.340
And we're sort of perturbatively
removing those problems,

00:53:56.340 --> 00:53:59.393
perturbatively going towards
the Wilsonian picture.

00:53:59.393 --> 00:54:01.060
And the nice thing
about this is that we

00:54:01.060 --> 00:54:03.850
can maintain the symmetries,
still gauge invariant, still

00:54:03.850 --> 00:54:05.157
Lorentz invariant.

00:54:19.580 --> 00:54:22.130
And we don't get the full sort
of power of the Wilsonian,

00:54:22.130 --> 00:54:25.560
but we get closer to it.

00:54:25.560 --> 00:54:27.470
And we can, in some
sense, get as close

00:54:27.470 --> 00:54:31.850
as we want, again, by sort
of perturbing this from order

00:54:31.850 --> 00:54:34.020
by order.

00:54:34.020 --> 00:54:37.160
So what we introduce is
power law dependence in R.

00:54:37.160 --> 00:54:39.987
And that power law
dependence, it's

00:54:39.987 --> 00:54:41.570
the analog of the
power law dependence

00:54:41.570 --> 00:54:43.640
that would be in the
Wilsonian scheme.

00:54:43.640 --> 00:54:46.720
So when you have integrals like
this, you would have powers.

00:54:46.720 --> 00:54:48.470
There's nothing that
stops you from having

00:54:48.470 --> 00:54:51.200
a complicated function
of Q over lambda.

00:54:51.200 --> 00:54:54.770
And what we're saying is that
the dominant kind of power law

00:54:54.770 --> 00:54:57.320
sensitive terms here
and here are captured

00:54:57.320 --> 00:54:58.640
by making this scheme change.

00:55:23.690 --> 00:55:25.790
So we decide that we
like MS-bar because we

00:55:25.790 --> 00:55:31.330
have calculations that other
people have done hopefully.

00:55:31.330 --> 00:55:34.020
If they're three-loop
order, you certainly

00:55:34.020 --> 00:55:36.443
hope that someone else spent
two years of their life on it

00:55:36.443 --> 00:55:37.110
rather than you.

00:55:44.300 --> 00:55:52.940
And you can take and perturb
your results from MS-bar

00:55:52.940 --> 00:55:55.130
towards a gauge invariant,
Lorentz invariant

00:55:55.130 --> 00:56:00.450
version of the Wilsonian,
of the Wilsonian picture.

