01:00:07.920 --> 01:00:09.660
And it's very much
like our masses.

01:00:09.660 --> 01:00:14.280
There's some function
with an R in front.

01:00:14.280 --> 01:00:18.940
And we could formally
write down solutions to it.

01:00:18.940 --> 01:00:21.420
And we can explicitly
plug in results

01:00:21.420 --> 01:00:22.920
given how many
terms in the series

01:00:22.920 --> 01:00:25.480
we know in the MS-bar series.

01:00:28.330 --> 01:00:31.400
So all the anomalous dimensions
of this Wilson coefficient

01:00:31.400 --> 01:00:33.160
would be determined
by the MS-bar series,

01:00:33.160 --> 01:00:35.420
the original one,
because the scheme

01:00:35.420 --> 01:00:38.600
that redefining is set up so
that it uses those [INAUDIBLE]

01:00:38.600 --> 01:00:39.782
coefficients.

