It's the same kind
of structure as what

01:01:05.290 --> 01:01:14.008
we have for masses,
some gamma functions.

01:01:27.470 --> 01:01:30.730
And you can think
of this as some C0.

01:01:30.730 --> 01:01:33.620
If you want kind of to have
a more standard notation,

01:01:33.620 --> 01:01:37.700
you would say that this
is some U function.

01:01:37.700 --> 01:01:40.030
And this is a bit of abuse
of notation, actually, here

01:01:40.030 --> 01:01:46.363
because it's additive,
not multiplicative.

01:01:46.363 --> 01:01:48.280
But if you allow me to
put this guy into here,

01:01:48.280 --> 01:01:50.660
then I could always
write it this way.

01:01:50.660 --> 01:01:52.880
And I'll just do
