01:05:14.820 --> 01:05:17.422
But when you think about
whether that's actually right

01:05:17.422 --> 01:05:19.380
and you calculate the
higher order corrections,

01:05:19.380 --> 01:05:23.160
you find that you're moving
away from the data, right?

01:05:23.160 --> 01:05:24.700
And again, it's not convergent.

01:05:24.700 --> 01:05:27.100
Summing the logs
has not helped you.

01:05:27.100 --> 01:05:29.100
And that's because what
we're talking about here

01:05:29.100 --> 01:05:30.525
has nothing to do with logs.

01:05:30.525 --> 01:05:31.710
It has to do with powers.

01:05:31.710 --> 01:05:36.360
It's the renormalon that's
causing this problem, OK?

01:05:36.360 --> 01:05:40.050
So we could throw up our hands
and say, oh, it doesn't work.

01:05:40.050 --> 01:05:42.780
Or we could try to
do something better.

01:05:42.780 --> 01:05:45.750
So let me show you what happens
if we do some of this stuff

01:05:45.750 --> 01:05:48.190
that I've been
telling you about.

01:05:48.190 --> 01:05:52.462
So this guy has a u
equals 1 renormalon.

01:05:52.462 --> 01:05:55.200
You can check that very
