01:18:10.550 --> 01:18:13.400
theory with what
looks like a problem.

01:18:13.400 --> 01:18:15.460
It's got a fine tuning.

01:18:15.460 --> 01:18:17.877
So usually, if the whole notion
of effective field theory

01:18:17.877 --> 01:18:20.210
is against the idea that there
should be a fine tuning--

01:18:20.210 --> 01:18:21.860
because you're making
dimensional analysis

01:18:21.860 --> 01:18:22.693
estimates of things.

01:18:22.693 --> 01:18:25.310
If there's a fine tuning, that
means your dimensional analysis

01:18:25.310 --> 01:18:26.810
failed.

01:18:26.810 --> 01:18:31.010
In this example, we'll see that
